GitHub Instructions for Linux

1. Install GitHub through the command line
	$ sudo apt-get install git

2. Configure your username and e-mail
	$ git config --global user.name "Enter username WITH the quotations"
	$ git config --global user.email "Enter email WITH the quotations"

3. Make a new directory called DataStructures in your documents
	$ git init DataStructures
	$ cd DataStructues

4. Clone GitHub repository to your computer
	$ git clone https://github.com/luigi741/COP4530.git

5. Pulling from the GitHub repository
	$ git pull origin master

6. Pushing to the GitHub repository
	// This following command stages all files to be committed/pushed to the repository
	$ git add .
		// To unstage use $ git reset HEAD FILENAME
	$ git commit -m "Description of this push/commit"
	$ git push origin master